CIO Randy Mott On How IT Put GM On A Profitable Path 
GM CIO Mott: Own IT To Own Innovation
Insourcing Key To GM’s Turnaround
GM CEO Akerson Is An IT Believer



        By   
Paul McDougall 
 | November 27, 2013 | 


Bankrupt and in need of a bailout, GM appeared headed for the wrecking yard in 2009. Fast forward, and CEO Dan Akerson’s transformation program has the iconic automaker back in the black. In a CruxialCIO exclusive, CIO Randy Mott explains how he reengineered GM’s IT unit to support the turnaround. 



Situation 


Solutions 


Takeaways 

















 













 




    Change Agent: CM CIO Randy Mott is driving innovation that’s helping the company build vehicles, like the 2013 Camaro Coupe, more efficiently.  GM

 





